info.headline: Flood Advisory issued September 22 at 11:41PM EDT until September 23 at 1:45AM EDT by NWS Key West FL
info.description:
* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected.
* WHERE...For the eastern Lower Keys, from Summerland Key to Big Pine Key.
* WHEN...Until 145 AM EDT.
* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 1140 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to thunderstorms. Minor flooding is ongoing or expected to begin shortly in the advisory area. Between 1.5 and 2.5 inches of rain have fallen. - Additional rainfall amounts of 1 to 2 inches are expected over the area. This additional rain will result in minor flooding. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... Little Torch Key, Ramrod Key, Big Pine Key, Middle Torch Key, Little Palm Island Resort and Summerland Key. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction:
Do not drive your vehicle into areas where the water covers the roadway. The water depth may be too great to allow your car to cross safely.
Be aware of your surroundings and do not drive on flooded roads.

parameter.value: FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 145 AM EDT TUESDAY
